Egyptian Stocks: Amer Group and Pioneers Holding Were Active

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-04-12T14:54:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/egyptian-stocks-amer-group-and-pioneers-holding-are-active.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (CASE)  fell
for a fourth day, losing 1.4 percent to 5,202.47, the lowest in
almost three weeks, at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following stocks rose or fell in Egypt. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Amer Group Holding (AMER)  , the Cairo-based resorts
operator, declined 3.3 percent to 1.17 Egyptian pounds, the
lowest level since listing shares in November. The number of
tourist visiting Egypt tumbled 46 percent in the first quarter
to 1.9 million from the year-earlier period amid the revolution
that toppled the country’s government, Tourism Minister Mounir
Fakhry Abdel Nour said late yesterday.  Pioneers Holding (PIOH EY) fell 2.3 percent to 2.11 pounds,
the lowest since shares listed in June 2008.  Egypt ’s second-
biggest publicly traded investment bank said 2010 profit plunged
90 percent to 10.9 million pounds ($1.83 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
